title: 1  Sample Description
text: Participants (N = 66) were randomly assigned to either the BAM (N=38) or the Body Project (N=28) intervention. Of these, XX attended the interventions virtually (BAM: N=XX, BP: N=XX) beginning 09/20 and ending 02/22 due to the pandemic and XX attended in-person sessions (BAM: N=XX, BP: N=XX) from MM/YY to MM/YY. Participants ranged in age from 18 – 28 years with the average age being 21.23 years. Participants were mostly women (95.45%) and and the most commonly reported race was White (N = 75.76%). Furthermore, the majority of participants identified as heterosexual (69.7%) followed by bisexual (27.27%). At the time of the intervention, 64 participants reported being students. For a study flow diagram, see figure Y.
